alert.note: Alert for Levy (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flash Flood Warning issued June 20 at 10:10AM EDT until June 20 at 11:45AM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tampa Bay Ruskin has issued a * Flash Flood Warning for... Levy County in northern Florida... * Until 1145 AM EDT. * At 1010 AM EDT, emergency management reported thunderstorms producing heavy rain across the warned area. Several roads are closed around the City of Williston with cars reported stranded in water. Between 6 and 7 inches of rain have fallen. Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are possible in the warned area. Flash flooding is already occurring. HAZARD...Flash flooding caused by thunderstorms. SOURCE...Emergency management reported. IMPACT...Flash flooding of small creeks and streams, urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses as well as other poor drainage and low-lying areas. * Some locations that will experience flash flooding include... Williston, Williston Highlands and Williston Municipal Airport. FLASH FLOOD...OBSERVED
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.
